my mom, when she was little, use to sit in the back of my granpas pickup truck with her brother and eat vienna sausages+beans while trying to figure out what pictures the clouds made, all day long. i like my mom. when i was around 8 or 9, the house next door to me was a crack house. all these people would stay up to the wee hours in the morning and drug deal and play basketball all night long. there was a few drive by shootings every now and then at the house. after a while this got really annoying so everyone started calling the cops every now and then. they assumed it was us and broke into our house while we were camping off at lake whitney. it so happened that our other neighbor was walking in our alley during this time and heard them, so she called the popo. they were caught a few days later in dallas and only one went to jail and the rest moved out. after they moved out, the house was empty for a couple of years. then some crazy german couple moved in about a year or two ago. a few months ago the wife/lady that lives there woke up with burns all over half of her body, not knowing what happened to her. turns out her husband, while he was out of town on "business", hired the neighboors two doors down from us (that own two monkeys) to kill her for a nice sum of money. the police are still investagating it and found drugs in what she was drinking that night. the guy is now living with somebody else. crazy house.
